{"type":"item.completed","item":{"id":"item_60","type":"agent_message","text":"The cleanest fix would be to stop using a fresh BC provider for test-data generation at all. I’m probing whether the PKCS#8 encryption helper works with the built-in JCE provider; if it does, I can keep the test focused on the driver’s BC decryption path and drop the noisy native-image provider flag."}}
